---
// src/pages/projects/capsule-closet.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Capsule Closet Ecosystem | Ean Cummings">
  <article class="project-deep-dive animate-fade-in">
    
    <!-- ==================== 1. CINEMATIC HEADER ==================== -->
    <header class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-hero-container">
        <span class="pro-tag-badge">Generative Artificial Intelligence</span>
        <h1 class="pro-headline">Capsule Closet</h1>
        <p class="pro-subheading">
          A dynamic wardrobe platform deployed on Vercel that leverages the Gemini API suite to streamline outfit selection, synthesize virtual try-on models, and reduce decision fatigue.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="https://capsulecloset.vercel.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary-action">
            Launch Web App ↗
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-overlay"></div>
    </header>

    <!-- ==================== 2. AI INTEGRATION & WORKFLOW ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">01 / AI Architecture</span>
        <h2>Multi-Model Generative Logic</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          To parse unstructured wardrobe photos into actionable data, the application relies on <strong>Gemini 2.5 Flash</strong> to detect items and return structured JSON labels containing categories, colors, and styles. Once the inventory is staged, <strong>Gemini 3 Pro Preview</strong> acts as the reasoning engine, cross-referencing wardrobe metadata to propose curated outfits via pure text prompts.
        </p>
        <p>
          For the visual rendering, the platform utilizes <strong>Gemini 2.5 Flash Image (Nano Banana)</strong> to perform image-to-image synthesis, generating believable virtual try-on models wearing the selected garments. To ensure scalability, responsible AI usage, and cost control, I engineered a secure API key management system that allows users to supply and authenticate their own Gemini credentials locally.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Premium Dual Photo Showcase Grid -->
        <div class="product-media-gallery">
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/capsule-shot.png" alt="Capsule Closet Web Dashboard Interface" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">The React-based web interface featuring the AI Stylist module, wardrobe inventory grid, and avatar dressing room.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/capsule-workflow.png" alt="Capsule Closet System Workflow Diagram" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">System pipeline mapping user inputs to Vercel serverless functions and dedicated Gemini model endpoints.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ==================== 3. SOFTWARE & DEPLOYMENT TOPOLOGY ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">02 / Infrastructure</span>
        <h2>Vercel & Client-Side Architecture</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          The application is built on a <strong>React and TypeScript</strong> foundation managed by the Vite build tool. To securely bridge the public web app and the generative AI models, the system relies on <strong>Vercel serverless functions</strong> to handle backend logic, separating the client from the API boundary.
        </p>
        <p>
          Handling high-resolution images from mobile device cameras posed a risk to browser local storage limits and latency. To mitigate this, we implemented client-side image resizing and JPEG compression before the data hits the server. Users can maintain persistent wardrobe states via local storage or by downloading their entire parsed closet as a structured JSON file for future sessions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ==================== 4. TECH SPECS DASHBOARD ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row border-top-only">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">03 / Tech Specs</span>
        <h2>System Specifications</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <div class="specs-mini-grid">
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Generative Vision</h4>
            <p>Gemini 2.5 Flash & Gemini 2.5 Flash Image</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Reasoning Engine</h4>
            <p>Gemini 3 Pro Preview</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Frontend Stack</h4>
            <p>React, TypeScript, Vite</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Cloud Infrastructure</h4>
            <p>Vercel Serverless Functions</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>

<!-- ==================== STYLES ==================== -->
<style>
  .project-deep-dive {
    max-width: 1024px;
    width: min(100%, 92%);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  /* --- Advanced Hero Styling Layering --- */
  .project-hero {
    min-height: 50vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding-top: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 60px;
    background-color: #000000;
  }

  /* Layers the custom web app asset cleanly beneath layout masks */
  .project-hero::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4) 0%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75) 65%, #000000 92%, #000000 100%), url('/images/capsule-shot.png');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .project-hero-container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
    padding: 0 4px;
  }

  .pro-tag-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(47, 128, 237, 0.4);
    border-radius: 100px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
  }

  .pro-headline {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
    color: #ffffff;
    text-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75), 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }

  .pro-subheading {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: #e8e8ed;
    max-width: 720px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  /* --- Hero CTA Button --- */
  .hero-actions {
    margin-top: 32px;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 12; /* Elevates interactivity above the grid mesh */
  }

  .btn-primary-action {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    background-color: var(--text-primary);
    color: var(--bg-black);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    border-radius: 100px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }
  
  .btn-primary-action:hover {
    background-color: #e8e8ed;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .grid-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  /* --- Row Layout Mechanics --- */
  .pro-content-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    padding: 64px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .border-top-only {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .pro-content-row {
      grid-template-columns: 3fr 5fr;
      gap: 64px;
    }
    .pro-sidebar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 100px;
    }
  }

  .row-num {
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pro-sidebar h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .pro-main-body {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .pro-main-body p {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  /* --- Upgraded Dual Photo Showcase Grid --- */
  .product-media-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .product-media-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .media-panel-box {
    background: #0d0d0e;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .media-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 240px; 
    object-fit: cover; 
    object-position: top center; 
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: block;
  }

  .media-caption {
    display: block;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding: 0 4px;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* --- Technical Spec Breakdown --- */
  .specs-mini-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card h4 {
    margin: 0 0 6px 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .spec-mini-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
</style>